You'll find the U.S.A. interesting-exciting-beautiful.
New York is generally considered the most vital and stimulat-
ing city on earth. There's an endless variety of things to see and
do ... smart shops, theaters, fine restaurants, the best in music
and art-and, most inspiring of all, the United Nations. To view
the city from the top of a skyscraper is like having the world
spread at your feet.
New England is the cradle of America and Boston is its princi-
pal city. There you will find quaint old streets, shops and his-
toric buildings. Some of America's most attractive scenery is
in this vicinity.
Your first impression of the Middle West will be one of space.
Chicago is the commercial hub of this vast area and Detroit its
most productive manufacturing center.
In the Pacific Northwest you will see nature at her most ex-
travagant .. mighty forests of redwood trees, towering water-
falls, snowcapped mountains. The principal cities of Seattle and
Portland extend a friendly welcome to all visitors.
On the West coast you will find American living at its best
where life in the outdoors sets the pace. The California coastline
ranges from rocky cliffs and a pounding surf to broad beaches
gently touched by the blue Pacific. Both San Francisco and
Los Angeles enjoy a mild climate year round.
The Southern states offer a great variety of climate and scen-
ery-from the lazy land along the Mississippi to the tropical
splendor of Florida with its sun-drenched beaches fringed with
graceful palms.
The whole United States is yours
when you fly PAN AMERICAN.
